paws 0.1.10

Returns a list of contacts

Source: R/groundstation_operations.R
groundstation_list_contacts.Rd

Returns a list of contacts.

If statusList contains AVAILABLE, the request must include groundStation, missionprofileArn, and satelliteArn.

groundstation_list_contacts(endTime, groundStation, maxResults,
  missionProfileArn, nextToken, satelliteArn, startTime, statusList)

Arguments

endTime

[required] End time of a contact.
groundStation

Name of a ground station.
maxResults

Maximum number of contacts returned.
missionProfileArn

ARN of a mission profile.
nextToken

Next token returned in the request of a previous ListContacts call. Used to get the next page of results.
satelliteArn

ARN of a satellite.
startTime

[required] Start time of a contact.
statusList

[required] Status of a contact reservation.

Request syntax

svc$list_contacts(
  endTime = as.POSIXct(
    "2015-01-01"
  ),
  groundStation = "string",
  maxResults = 123,
  missionProfileArn = "string",
  nextToken = "string",
  satelliteArn = "string",
  startTime = as.POSIXct(
    "2015-01-01"
  ),
  statusList = list(
    "AVAILABLE"|"AWS_CANCELLED"|"AWS_FAILED"|"CANCELLED"|"CANCELLING"|"COMPLETED"|"FAILED"|"FAILED_TO_SCHEDULE"|"PASS"|"POSTPASS"|"PREPASS"|"SCHEDULED"|"SCHEDULING"
  )
)
